{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"28b7ec77-ab96-494c-81b1-2a2d6f98e101","content":"No files found in the working directory, so I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML root element:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is adding:\n- `xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"` — namespace import\n- `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — enables compiled bindings\n\n**2. Catch binding errors at build time** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding failures as build errors (net9.0+) -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith `x:DataType` set, the XAML compiler resolves bindings at compile time. If you typo a property name (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`), you'll get a **build error** instead of a silent runtime failure.\n\n**3. Opting out locally** — if a specific binding must stay dynamic (e.g., a `DataTemplate` with a different type), use `x:DataType=\"\"` on that element to disable compiled bindings for its subtree.\n\n**Quick checklist:**\n| Before | After |\n|---|---|\n| No `x:DataType` | `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on root |\n| Bindings resolved at runtime | Bindings resolved at compile time |\n| Typos fail silently | Typos produce build errors |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"73b0847e-5bed-4ca2-8f2d-210693d3f90c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The files don't exist yet. The user is asking me to help them convert their page. Since there are no files in the working directory, I'll provide guidance on how to convert the page to use compiled bindings. Let me explain the conversion clearly.","outputTokens":603},"id":"aa541bc9-dd88-4a7c-b1df-07feaa2f08fe","timestamp":"2026-04-09T15:16:55.504Z","parentId":"5ed53269-8dcf-4148-81f1-8cba12f72a89"}
